  "doc_id": "41534",
  "text": "The polymorphism +49 A> G (rs231775) of gene CTLA-4, which promotes the exchange of amino acid threonine for alanine at position 17, has emerged as the natural candidate, among polymorphisms of CTLA-4 gene, because of the ability to promote functional changes of protein CTLA-4. Kouki et al., [CITATION_1] showed a higher frequency of genotype GG or AG at position 49 of the CTLA-4 gene in GD patients, and lesser control over proliferation and clonal expansion of T cells. Whereas Maurer et al [CITATION_2] found differences in the pool of intracellular CTLA-4 protein, prompting imbalance in the expression and competition between CTLA-4 and CD28 on the surface of T cells, possibly modifying the suppression of T cells and generating larger quantities of inflammatory cytokines.",
